title: Discrete bending energy
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Let $$\gamma \in \mathcal M_n$$ and let $$\kappa_i \in \ropenI{0,\pi}$$ such that $$\cos\kappa_i = \lang T_{i-1},T_i\rang.$$ the //discrete bending energy// of $$\gamma$$ is then defined by
$$
E(\gamma) \coloneqq
-\frac 1 2 \sum_i \log\left(
  \frac{1 + \cos\kappa_i}{2}
\right).
$$